  "text": "Image: MachineGames/Bethesda Softworks via PolygonJeffrey Parkin (he/him) has been writing video game guides for Polygon for almost seven years. He has learned to love just about every genre of game that exists.There’s a nondescript chest you’ll find early in your exploration of Gizeh in Indiana Jones and the Great Circle. It’s about halfway between the Great Sphinx and the Tomb of Khentkawes I. Turns out, this chest is the conclusion to a mystery called “Bright Future” that you can begin elsewhere.Our Indiana Jones and the Great Circle guide will show you how to start the “Bright Future” mystery and how to find the chest code.Table of ContentsHow to start the ‘Bright Future’ mysterySearch Pohl’s bunk in ‘Bright Future’‘Bright Future’ chest location and codeHow to start the ‘Bright Future’ mysteryImage: MachineGames/Bethesda Softworks via PolygonTo start the “Bright Future” mystery, you’ll need to head into the Nazi Vehicle Garage in Gizeh. You’ll find it to the west of the Great Sphinx, right next to the Nazi Recreation Area near the center of the map.Image: MachineGames/Bethesda Softworks via PolygonInside the large tent in the middle of the garage area, look for the radio equipment at the south end. There, you’ll find Pohl’s Note.Search Pohl’s bunk in ‘Bright Future’Image: MachineGames/Bethesda Softworks via PolygonThe next objective in “Bright Future” is to search Pohl’s Bunk. Head east and into the tent right next to the garage area’s entrance.Image: MachineGames/Bethesda Softworks via PolygonCheck the bottom bunk on the right side to find the Nazi Note containing a chest code — 0926.‘Bright Future’ chest location and codeImage: MachineGames/Bethesda Softworks via PolygonThere’s a good chance you found the locked “Bright Future” chest earlier in your travels. It’s along the road about halfway between the Great Sphinx and the Tomb of Khentkawes I, not too far from the Gizeh Workers Area.Image: MachineGames/Bethesda Softworks via PolygonClick in the code from the Nazi Note to open the chest, but be prepared to run away.Pohl wasn’t really as generous as his note claimed (he’s a Nazi, after all), so all that’s waiting for you inside the chest is a lot of dynamite that’s about to blow up in your face.For more Indiana Jones and the Great Circle guides, here’s where to find the “Cloud Atlas” chest code.See More: GuidesIndiana Jones and the Great Circle guidesPCPlayStationXboxIndiana Jones and the Great Circle",
